    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Museums containing collections dealing with the properties of natural objects, plants, or animals, such as preserved specimens of birds, mammals, insects, and plants; rocks, minerals, and fossils. These museums have their origins in the cabinets of curiosities built up by prominent individuals in Europe during the Renaissance and Enlightenment.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Musea met collecties die verband houden met de eigenschappen van natuurlijke objecten, planten of dieren, zoals bewaard gebleven specimens van vogels, zoogdieren, insecten, planten, stenen, mineralen en fossielen. Deze musea hebben hun oorsprong in de rariteitenkabinetten die tijdens de Renaissance en de verlichting door vooraanstaande personen in Europa werden opgericht.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>藏品包含自然物件、植物或動物等資產，如鳥類、哺乳動物、昆蟲和植物的防腐標本；以及岩石、礦物和化石的博物館。這種博物館源於歐洲文藝復興時期與啟蒙時代之顯要名人所造的珍物陳列室。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
